pr_description:
BREAKING CHANGE:
- Removed EntityRecord
- Removed SimpleResource
- New BaseResource
- RestFetch, FetchMutate, FetchGet args change (FetchMutate<Params, Body> -> FetchMutate<[Params, Body]>)
- Remove deprecated 'Shape' methods (pre-endpoints)

### Motivation
<!--
Does this solve a bug? Enable a new use-case? Improve an existing behavior? Concrete examples are helpful here.
-->
https://resthooks.io/blog/2021/08/29/Experimental-useController#new-hiearchy

#### Support variable arg REST Endpoints

```ts
class MyResource {
  static current<T extends typeof Resource>(this: T): RestEndpoint<FetchGet<[]>, T, undefined> {
    return super.endpoint().extend({
      schema: this,
    });
  }
  static delete<T extends typeof Resource>(this: T): RestEndpoint<FetchMutate<[id: number]>, schema.Delete<T>, true> {
    return super.delete().extend({
      getOptimisticResponse: (snap, id) => id,
      schema: new schema.Delete(this),
    });
  }
}
```

#### BaseResource - all the Resource with none of the endpoints. Start your endpoint definitions from scratch.

- Won't come with endpoints that it doesn't have
- Doesn't have to conform to inheritance hierarchy of base endpoints

```ts
// read-only
class MyResource extends BaseResource {
  static detail<T extends typeof Resource>(
    this: T,
  ): RestEndpoint<
    FetchGet<[id:number]>,
    T,
    undefined
  > {
    return this.endpoint().extend({
        schema: this,
      });
  }
}
```

### Solution
<!--
What is the solution here from a high level. What are the key technical decisions and why were they made?
-->
Pulled from experimental, but did not include pagination

Split into 4 parts as intended to be landed in 4 commits rather than squashed.

