pr_description:
### Motivation
<!--
Does this solve a bug? Enable a new use-case? Improve an existing behavior? Concrete examples are helpful here.
-->
Part 1 of 2.
Programmatic access. Global referential equality and computational efficiency.

### Solution
<!--
What is the solution here from a high level. What are the key technical decisions and why were they made?
-->

#### [schema.All](https://resthooks.io/rest/api/All)

Returns all entities found. Supports polymorphism.

#### [Query](https://resthooks.io/rest/api/Query)

Endpoint without fetch (usable with [useCache()](https://resthooks.io/docs/api/useCache)). Great to use with [schema.All](https://resthooks.io/rest/api/All)

#### Simplest

```ts
const allUsers = new Query(new schema.All(User));

useCache(allUsers);
```

#### Polymorphic

```ts
class Cat extends IDEntity {
  readonly type = 'Cat';
  index = 0;
}
class Dog extends IDEntity {
  readonly type = 'dogs';
  index = 0;
}
class Person extends IDEntity {
  readonly type = 'people';
  index = 0;
}
const getAnimals = new Query(new schema.All(
    {
      Cat: Cat,
      dogs: Dog,
      people: Person,
    },
    input => input.type || 'dogs',
  ),
  (entries, [{ asc }]) {
    const sorted = [...entries].sort((a, b) => a.index - b.index);
    if (asc) return sorted;
    return sorted.reverse();
  },
);

useCache(getAnimals, { asc: true });
```

### Future work

- Improve caching
  - Index updates for All
- schema.Collection

