pr_description:
### Motivation

- Reduce API footprint
    - Reduce bundle size
    - Easier to learn
    - Less code to write
- Writing [getOptimisticResponse() ](https://dataclient.io/rest/api/RestEndpoint#getoptimisticresponse)and other concepts based on state are significantly cleaner
- eliminates the need to refer to endpoints or resources in endpoint arguments (which caused a *lot* of typing challenges)

### Solution

- Remove Query and Index endpoints
- useCache() can take any [Queryable](https://dataclient.io/rest/api/schema#queryable) [schemas ](https://dataclient.io/rest/api/schema)directly.
- Add [schema.Query()](https://dataclient.io/rest/api/Query)
  - This only accepts [Queryable](https://dataclient.io/rest/api/schema#queryable) schemas.
- `Collection.query(queryFn)` is shorthand for taking an existing collection and just adding the process (like [Collection.push](https://dataclient.io/rest/api/Collection#push), returns a [schema](https://dataclient.io/rest/api/schema))

#### Mechanism

[Schemas ](https://dataclient.io/rest/api/schema)now have Args - this can be used to get possible args in [useQuery()](https://dataclient.io/docs/api/useQuery)

#### Examples

```jsx
class User extends Entity {
  id = '';
  username = '';

  pk() { return this.id;}
  static indexes = ['username'] as const;
}
```

#### Before

```jsx
const UserIndex = new Index(User)

const bob = useCache(UserIndex, { username: 'bob' });
```

#### After

```jsx
const bob = useQuery(User, { username: 'bob' });
```

#### Before

```jsx
const getUserCount = new Query(
  new schema.All(User),
  (entries, { isAdmin } = { }) => {
    if (isAdmin !== undefined)
      return entries.filter(user => user.isAdmin === isAdmin).length;
    return entries.length;
  },
);

const userCount = useCache(getUserCount);
const adminCount = useCache(getUserCount, { isAdmin: true });
```

#### After

```jsx
const getUserCount = new schema.Query(
  new schema.All(User),
  (entries, { isAdmin } = { }) => {
    if (isAdmin !== undefined)
      return entries.filter(user => user.isAdmin === isAdmin).length;
    return entries.length;
  },
);

const userCount = useQuery(getUserCount);
const adminCount = useQuery(getUserCount, { isAdmin: true });
```

#### Before

```tsx
export const PostResource = createResource({
  path: '/posts/:id',
  schema: Post,
}).extend(Base => ({
  vote: new RestEndpoint({
    path: '/posts/:id/vote',
    method: 'POST',
    body: undefined,
    schema: Post,
    getOptimisticResponse(snapshot, { id }) {
      const { data } = snapshot.getResponse(Base.get, { id });
      if (!data) throw new AbortOptimistic();
      return {
        id,
        votes: data.votes + 1,
      };
    },
  }),
}));
```

#### After

```tsx
export const PostResource = createResource({
  path: '/posts/:id',
  schema: Post,
}).extend('vote',
  {
    path: '/posts/:id/vote',
    method: 'POST',
    body: undefined,
    schema: Post,
    getOptimisticResponse(snapshot, { id }) {
      const post = snapshot.get(Post, { id });
      if (!post) throw new AbortOptimistic();
      return {
        id,
        votes: post.votes + 1,
      };
    },
  },
);
```

### TODO

- [x] Add [controller.get ](https://dataclient.io/docs/api/Controller#get)and [snapshot.get](https://dataclient.io/docs/api/Snapshot#get)
- [x] Add [useQuery](https://dataclient.io/docs/api/useQuery)
- [x] Add [Query schema](https://dataclient.io/rest/api/Query)
- [x] Handle Union inference needing extra arguments (useQuery should not use generics for args, but should accept schema's args, we need to do something about url using these extra args...)
- [x] Remove queryEndpoint, Index
- [x] Update docs to use [snap.get() ](https://dataclient.io/docs/api/Snapshot#get)in [getOptimisticResponse](https://dataclient.io/rest/api/RestEndpoint#getoptimisticresponse)
- [x] Docs: Schema table, add Query schema, remove Query and Index from endpoints
- [x] docs: update README references
- [x] docs: Add blog draft with changes

### Followup

- [ ] infer -> buildKey?
- [ ] Infer caching
- [ ] codemod and link in release docs
- [ ] Future release:
  - [ ] ctrl.set()



### Open Questions

- Should we get rid of AbortOptimistic and simply abort on any exception?
  - If so we could simply try to access data and if it doesn't exist, it would abort
  - If we lied about the types here to make types work then it wouldn't work well for middlewares that don't want to throw. We could change types just for snapshot but would probably be unexpected
  - Answer: No, the explicit handling makes it more readable; This will definitely silence errors that people can easily fix.

