pr_description:
### Motivation
<!--
Does this solve a bug? Enable a new use-case? Improve an existing behavior? Concrete examples are helpful here.
-->
Final step to store only pojos in state.
Also consolidates logic where dependencies already exist

### Solution
<!--
What is the solution here from a high level. What are the key technical decisions and why were they made?
-->

#### Reducer processing receive

```ts
        const { result, entities, indexes, entityMeta } = normalize(
          action.payload,
          action.meta.schema,
          state.entities,
          state.indexes,
          state.entityMeta,
          action.meta,
        );
        let results = {
          ...state.results,
          [action.meta.key]: result,
        };
        results = applyUpdatersToResults(results, result, action.meta.updaters);
        if (action.meta.update) {
          const updaters = action.meta.update(
            result,
            ...(action.meta.args || []),
          );
          Object.keys(updaters).forEach(key => {
            results[key] = updaters[key](results[key]);
          });
        }
        return {
          entities,
          indexes,
          results,
          entityMeta,
          meta: {
            ...state.meta,
            [action.meta.key]: {
              date: action.meta.date,
              expiresAt: action.meta.expiresAt,
              prevExpiresAt: state.meta[action.meta.key]?.expiresAt,
            },
          },
          optimistic: filterOptimistic(state, action),
        };
```

#### Full summary

- Normalize returns entityMeta
- existing store values are updated (immutably) during normalize so reducer is simply replacing them
- all extra args are optional and it is still backwards compatible with previous calls
- entityMeta is added to return object; since this can be ignored return value is also still backward comaptible
- fixed: time comparison to avoid race conditions now applies to non-merging cases like deletes
- due to snapshotting normalizr output those tests either do a basic match on entityMeta, or mock time to be deterministic
- @rest-hooks/experimental Delete, which is for new entities, uses process instead of fromJS to preprocess for finding PK

